The error message `The given file contains a sorry on the last line, column 38.` indicates that the Lean 4 proof has an unresolved `sorry` tactic at the very end of the file. This usually means that a proof obligation was not fully discharged, or a placeholder was left incomplete.

Looking at the context, the last part of the proof attempts to show that for each element `A` in the set `S'` (which represents non-central conjugacy classes), the cardinality of its conjugacy class is 1. This is a key step in verifying that the conditions for using the orbit-stabilizer theorem are met.

