If `n_k A = 1`, then `q ^ n - 1 = q - 1 + (q ^ n - 1) / (q - 1) + ∑_{B ≠ A} ...`.
This would mean `(q ^ n - 1) / (q - 1)` is an integer. This is true if `q ^ n ≡ 1 \pmod{q-1}`. Since `q = Fintype.card Z`, and `n = Fintype.card Rˣ / Fintype.card Zˣ`, we have `q ^ n = (Fintype.card Z) ^ (Fintype.card Rˣ / Fintype.card Zˣ)`. Since `Fintype.card Rˣ = q^n - 1` and `Fintype.card Zˣ = q - 1`, we have `q^n = (q-1) * (q^n - 1)/(q-1) + 1`. This is `q^n = (q^n - 1)/(q-1) * (q-1) + 1 = q^n - 1 + 1 = q^n`. This is consistent.
